cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper deals with deep convolutional neural networks and their optimization through pruning and structured sparsity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of particle filtering for deciding the importance of network connections, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for direct computational resource savings, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the reduction in storage size, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
